        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued September 5 at 11:22PM PDT by NWS Portland OR</headline>
        <description>At 1122 PM PDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm near
Jefferson, or near Albany, moving north at 15 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 40 mph and half inch hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor hail damage to vegetation is
possible.

Locations impacted include...
Albany, Jefferson, Millersburg, Buena Vista, and North Albany.

This includes the following highways in Oregon...
Interstate 5 between mile markers 233 and 245.
U.S. Highway 20 east of Albany between mile markers 1 and 10.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
